Philippines Stocks: Aboitiz Power, GMA Network, Lepanto Mining

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-08-03T04:34:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/philippines-stocks-aboitiz-power-gma-network-philex-mining.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index sank 1.2 percent to
4,488.45, the sharpest loss since May 31.  Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)  , which owns power plants and
electricity retailers, declined 1.2 percent to 31.95 pesos, the
lowest since July 21, after the stock was cut to “neutral”
from “outperform” by Dante Tinga, analyst at Credit Suisse
Group AG.  GMA Network Inc. (GMA7)  (GMA7 PM), the second-largest television
and radio network operator, fell 0.7 percent to 6.85 pesos, the
lowest close since July 4. The company reported second-quarter
profit of 521 million pesos ($12.3 million), it said in a
statement yesterday, without giving a comparison. GMA had a
profit of 834.07 million pesos in the same quarter last year,
data compiled by Bloomberg show.  Lepanto Consolidated Mining (LCB)  Co advanced to a
record after the company said it’s continuing to drill in its
Far Southeast project in Benguet, which contains “vast
reserves” of gold, according to a Philippine Daily Inquirer
report today. Lepanto Class B shares (LCB PM), which have no
ownership restriction, jumped 1.5 percent to 1.33 pesos, the
highest close based on prices going back to January 1990. Its
Class A shares, which are reserved for Filipinos, gained 1.7
percent to 1.22 pesos, also an all-time high.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
